Here is a list of [[syllabic abbreviations]]:

* '''[[bit]]''' from ''[[Binary numeral system|binary]]'' and ''[[numerical digit|digit]]''
* '''[[Capcom]]'''; from ''Capsule Communicator''.
* '''[[Codec]]'''; from ''compressor'' and ''decompressor''.  Computer function that modifies the format of a file.
* '''[[Internet]]''' from ''international/interglobal/interchanged'' and ''network''
* '''[[Interpol]]''', from ''international'' and ''police''
* '''[[Konami]]''', names of Kagemasa '''Ko'''zuki, Yoshinobu '''Na'''kama, Hiro '''M'''atsuda, and Shokichi '''I'''shihara
* '''[[Modem]]'''; from ''modulator'' and ''demodulator''.  This device connects computers to the Internet.
* '''[[multicart]]''' from ''multiple'' and ''cartridge''.  This kind of cartridge consists of multiple games in one (e.g. 76,000-in-1 from [[Power Player Super Joy III]]).
* '''[[Pixel]]'''; from ''picture'' and ''element''.  This is a unit on a computer display.
* '''[[sysop]]''' from ''[[system]]'' and ''[[operator]]''<!--Dubious: combines initial syllables-->
* '''[[texel]]''' from ''[[texture]]'' and ''element''



